==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chaparajos
<hw>Cha`pa*ra"jos</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Mex.
Sp.]</ety> <def>Overalls of sheepskin or leather, usually open at the
back, worn, esp. by cowboys, to protect the legs from thorny bushes, as
in the chaparral; -- called also <altname>chapareras</altname> or
colloq. <altname>chaps</altname>.</def> <mark>[Sp. Amer.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chapareras</ent>⟦br⟧
